<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-58-0648 </DOCNO><TEXT>To diagnose the diseases presenting with hematuria, various imaging methodsare important. Here we discuss mainly the malignant urological diseasessuch as cancers of the kidney, urinary bladder and prostate. For thedetermination of the stages in the renal cell cancer ultrasonographyand CT are the main tools. As for the bladder cancer it is said thatultrasound tomography is the best method for determining the stages.Prostatic cancer is also diagnosed by these imaging techniques. The ratesof correct diagnosis, however, are not satisfactory. Further effortsto improve the corret diagnosis should be made.</TEXT></DOC>